        "title": "Stalled remote streams fail fast",
        "summary": "Swarm-backed chat now surfaces explicit errors instead of leaving the UI stuck on the connecting state.",
        "items": [
          {
            "text": "Swarm session startup now waits for an explicit session_ready signal and a new turn watchdog broadcasts a terminal error if the remote runtime emits no events within 30s (or stays open past the 5-minute turn cap).",
            "commit_shas": [
              "33ad453f9e8aa1af16d78e0837800f09d16bec15"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "text": "Unsupported websocket frames from the harness are now translated into stream errors over the SSE channel, so chat unblocks instead of hanging behind keep-alives.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "33ad453f9e8aa1af16d78e0837800f09d16bec15"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          }
        ]
      },
